text: Aldworth is a village in Berkshire, England. Aldworth may also refer to: *Aldworth Manor – summer estate house in Harrisville, New Hampshire *Aldworth (Blackdown) – a house in Blackdown in the English county of Sussex built by Alfred Tennyson *Hannah Aldworth (died 1778) – English philanthropist *Thomas Aldworth (Reading MP) (fl. 1520–1577) – the 16th century mayor and member of parliament for Reading, England ==See also== *Alworth (disambiguation)
